# Icon Sizing Convention

`className="size-*"` is the canonical way to size `HugeiconsIcon`. The `size` prop is supplementary (SVG viewBox) — it must never be the only sizing mechanism for non-16px icons.

## Why

Shadcn's `buttonVariants` applies:

```css
[&_svg:not([class*='size-'])]:size-4
```

This forces any child SVG without a `size-*` class to 16px, overriding HTML `width`/`height` attributes set by the `size` prop.

## Pattern

```tsx
<HugeiconsIcon icon={SearchIcon} size={20} className="size-5" />
<HugeiconsIcon icon={SearchIcon} size={20} className="size-5 text-muted-foreground" />
```

## Quick Reference

| size prop | Tailwind class |
|-----------|---------------|
| 8 | size-2 |
| 10 | size-2.5 |
| 12 | size-3 |
| 14 | size-3.5 |
| 16 | size-4 (default — optional) |
| 20 | size-5 |
| 24 | size-6 |
| 32 | size-8 |
